div.p: 0. user triggers an action in "Page 1" that updates a react store
1. react store backup itself to local storage
2. local storage automatically triggers a StorageEvent, such event are not send to the originating window.

p.span: 3. event listener on "Page 2" listens to StorageEvent then dispatch a Flux event

div.p: 4. react store on "Page 2" receives the Flux event which makes it to reload from local storage
5. react store on "Page 2" emits a change event
